548
00:51:53,489 --> 00:51:56,909
l'm not gonna let you derail that
by hanging out with that trailer trash.

549
00:51:56,950 --> 00:51:58,952
You don't even know him.

550
00:51:58,994 --> 00:52:01,914
l know that kid better than you
ever will. lf your father was here--

551
00:52:01,955 --> 00:52:04,374
Look, sports, college--
that whole thing--

552
00:52:04,416 --> 00:52:06,502
that was my father's dream,
not mine.

553
00:52:06,543 --> 00:52:08,504
l never wanted any of it.

554
00:52:08,545 --> 00:52:11,048
Well, what do you want? Do you want
to live in the back of a truck?

555
00:52:11,048 --> 00:52:12,591
Do you want to collect welfare?

556
00:52:12,633 --> 00:52:14,635
You think
l wanted to come here?

557
00:52:14,676 --> 00:52:17,721
You think l wanted
to come and live with you?

558
00:52:25,395 --> 00:52:27,773
My brother and l
made a promise

559
00:52:27,815 --> 00:52:30,234
a long time ago:

560
00:52:30,234 --> 00:52:33,195
Should something happen
to either of us,

561
00:52:33,237 --> 00:52:35,572
we'd be there
for each other's kids.

562
00:52:37,783 --> 00:52:41,745
lt's not one you ever expect
to have to keep,

563
00:52:41,787 --> 00:52:45,332
and l'm not going back
on my word,

564
00:52:45,374 --> 00:52:48,335
but it's your life.

565
00:52:48,377 --> 00:52:50,671
You want to try it out
on your own,

566
00:52:50,712 --> 00:52:53,048
go ahead.

567
00:52:55,342 --> 00:52:56,844
You want me to get out?

568
00:52:56,885 --> 00:52:59,388
l want you to make a choice.

569
00:53:06,562 --> 00:53:10,524
Okay, well, we'll do things
my way for a while,

570
00:53:10,566 --> 00:53:14,194
just as long as we understand
each other.

571
00:53:14,236 --> 00:53:16,238
( sniffling )

572
00:53:26,165 --> 00:53:28,584
( door squeaks )

573
00:53:43,390 --> 00:53:45,809
( sobbing )

574
00:54:01,200 --> 00:54:02,784
Woman: Oh no.

575
00:54:11,752 --> 00:54:14,796
No.

576
00:54:14,838 --> 00:54:18,509
l haven't done anything.
l haven't done anything.

577
00:54:18,550 --> 00:54:20,636
Please.

578
00:54:20,677 --> 00:54:23,096
Graham:
Like l showed you.

579
00:54:23,138 --> 00:54:25,849
Woman:
Why are you doing this?

580
00:54:25,891 --> 00:54:28,977
How frightening
when it's our own flesh.

581
00:54:29,019 --> 00:54:31,396
Woman: No!

582
00:54:31,438 --> 00:54:32,981
No, stop.

583
00:54:33,023 --> 00:54:34,399
Graham:
Hold her still.

584
00:54:34,441 --> 00:54:37,027
Woman: No.

585
00:54:37,069 --> 00:54:38,821
- Graham: Do it!
- Please, please.

586
00:54:40,155 --> 00:54:42,032
- l don't think your heart's in this.
- No. No.

587
00:54:42,074 --> 00:54:44,159
( screaming )

588
00:54:48,455 --> 00:54:50,624
( woman continues screaming )

589
00:54:59,216 --> 00:55:02,553
( Martin gasping, coughing )

590
00:55:09,434 --> 00:55:13,313
Come on.
Come on.

591
00:55:13,355 --> 00:55:15,732
l'm not afraid
of you anymore.

592
00:55:15,774 --> 00:55:18,193
This is my house.

593
00:55:18,235 --> 00:55:20,612
l'm not gonna be like you--
condemned.

594
00:55:20,654 --> 00:55:23,198
l'm fixing what you broke!

595
00:55:23,240 --> 00:55:26,201
Go back to hell
where your bed is made.

596
00:55:26,243 --> 00:55:28,912
This is my house!

597
00:55:45,053 --> 00:55:47,055
( panting )

598
00:56:03,280 --> 00:56:05,407
( panting )

599
00:56:12,706 --> 00:56:14,875
( hammer pounding )

600
00:56:20,631 --> 00:56:23,258
- My dad trusted me.
- Jonathan will too.

601
00:56:23,300 --> 00:56:25,636
You just have to
give him a chance.

602
00:56:25,677 --> 00:56:28,013
Besides, it's not you
he doesn't trust.

603
00:56:28,055 --> 00:56:29,765
l can take care of myself.

604
00:56:29,806 --> 00:56:31,642
l know you can.

605
00:56:31,683 --> 00:56:33,852
He's just trying
to look out for you.

606
00:56:33,894 --> 00:56:36,021
Please.

607
00:56:37,397 --> 00:56:38,565
( sighs )

608
00:56:41,360 --> 00:56:43,904
What's he got
against William anyway?

609
00:56:43,946 --> 00:56:47,658
Oh, we've known Billy
since he was this high.

610
00:56:47,699 --> 00:56:51,078
He's had to deal with more
than his share of problems.

611
00:56:51,119 --> 00:56:53,121
That's not his fault.

612
00:56:53,163 --> 00:56:56,375
l mean, l think it's wonderful
how he takes care of his father,

613
00:56:56,416 --> 00:56:59,670
especially after what happened
to his mother.

614
00:56:59,670 --> 00:57:02,965
Well, she did that to herself.

615
00:57:03,006 --> 00:57:05,342
You can't give yourself
pneumonia.

616
00:57:07,010 --> 00:57:09,346
She didn't die of pneumonia.

617
00:57:09,346 --> 00:57:13,976
Billy's mother--
she killed herself.

618
00:57:14,017 --> 00:57:16,687
What?

619
00:57:16,728 --> 00:57:20,357
Hung herself in the garage.

620
00:57:24,611 --> 00:57:27,656
Billy was the one
who found her.

621
00:57:27,698 --> 00:57:30,576
lt was really hard on him.

622
00:57:30,617 --> 00:57:33,579
The doctors put him
on all sorts of medication.

623
00:57:33,620 --> 00:57:36,915
He's gotten in a lot of trouble
around town.

624
00:57:36,957 --> 00:57:40,210
l think Jonathan's just afraid
he's a little unstable.

625
00:57:40,252 --> 00:57:42,921
And his father-- well--

626
00:57:42,963 --> 00:57:44,464
Where are you going?

627
00:57:44,506 --> 00:57:46,633
l need to sort things out
in my head.

628
00:57:48,635 --> 00:57:50,637
Hey, Allison,
you want to play a game?

629
00:57:50,679 --> 00:57:52,681
Maybe later, okay?

630
00:57:52,723 --> 00:57:55,184
Where are you going?

631
00:58:31,094 --> 00:58:32,262
Hello?

632
00:58:36,808 --> 00:58:39,019
No, wait.

633
00:59:36,493 --> 00:59:38,495
( flies buzzing )

634
00:59:59,266 --> 01:00:01,310
Hello?

635
01:00:20,120 --> 01:00:23,081
Hey, are you okay?

636
01:00:24,124 --> 01:00:26,126
Wait.

637
01:00:52,486 --> 01:00:54,988
Are you okay?

638
01:00:56,240 --> 01:00:58,283
Are you in trouble?

639
01:01:14,550 --> 01:01:16,552
What are you doing down here?

640
01:01:25,644 --> 01:01:27,521
Are you in here?

641
01:01:50,252 --> 01:01:52,546
( quietly )
Oh my God.

642
01:02:38,300 --> 01:02:41,011
Martin.

643
01:03:01,865 --> 01:03:03,909
( rattling )

644
01:03:57,921 --> 01:03:59,631
Where are you?

645
01:04:02,801 --> 01:04:04,553
( Allison gasps )

646
01:04:04,595 --> 01:04:05,971
Wait. Come back.

647
01:04:19,485 --> 01:04:21,862
l'm not going to hurt you.

648
01:04:21,904 --> 01:04:23,530
l want to help you.

649
01:04:27,534 --> 01:04:29,203
ls your name Martin?

650
01:04:30,662 --> 01:04:32,873
Here, come with me.

651
01:04:32,915 --> 01:04:36,502
You can't stay here.
lt's not safe.

652
01:04:36,543 --> 01:04:38,712
What's wrong?

653
01:04:38,754 --> 01:04:41,840
You don't have to be afraid.

654
01:04:41,882 --> 01:04:43,884
You can trust me.

655
01:04:43,926 --> 01:04:45,802
You shouldn't be down here.

656
01:04:45,802 --> 01:04:49,890
( Allison screaming )
No! No!

657
01:04:49,932 --> 01:04:53,018
No! No! No!

658
01:04:54,019 --> 01:04:56,438
( panting )

659
01:05:03,779 --> 01:05:06,573
Good work.

660
01:05:12,496 --> 01:05:14,832
- l'm sure she's fine.
- How?

661
01:05:14,832 --> 01:05:17,251
She's just blowing off
some steam.

662
01:05:17,292 --> 01:05:20,003
No 17-year-old wants to be told
what to do.

663
01:05:25,092 --> 01:05:26,635
Not yet.

664
01:05:26,677 --> 01:05:29,847
l don't have any brothers or sisters
'cause Dad's lazy.

665
01:05:29,888 --> 01:05:32,850
And now he's
chased her away too.

666
01:05:32,850 --> 01:05:34,852
Way to go, Dad.

667
01:05:56,498 --> 01:05:58,667
( rat squeaking )

668
01:06:00,043 --> 01:06:01,628
( screaming )

669
01:06:01,670 --> 01:06:04,381
( screaming continues )

670
01:06:21,023 --> 01:06:23,442
( distant train horn blowing )

671
01:06:31,575 --> 01:06:33,160
She never came home
last night.

672
01:06:33,202 --> 01:06:36,121
l know.

673
01:06:36,163 --> 01:06:37,331
Where are you going?

674
01:06:37,372 --> 01:06:40,209
l'm gonna go find her.

675
01:06:45,255 --> 01:06:47,007
l need to speak to Allison.

676
01:06:47,049 --> 01:06:48,425
She's not here.

677
01:06:48,425 --> 01:06:50,636
lt's important.

678
01:06:50,677 --> 01:06:53,680
- She isn't here, Billy.
- We thought she was with you.

679
01:06:53,722 --> 01:06:56,099
No. She's been gone all night?

680
01:06:56,141 --> 01:06:57,643
Since yesterday.

681
01:06:57,684 --> 01:06:59,603
This is your goddamn fault.

682
01:06:59,645 --> 01:07:02,606
- Stop. Jonathan.
- Stay the hell away from her.

683
01:07:02,648 --> 01:07:03,816
- Jonathan.
- Don't push me.

684
01:07:03,857 --> 01:07:06,068
- Jonathan.
- You're no good.

685
01:07:06,109 --> 01:07:07,986
You're just like your old man--

686
01:07:08,028 --> 01:07:09,738
good for nothing.

687
01:07:09,780 --> 01:07:12,366
lt's okay.

688
01:07:12,407 --> 01:07:15,035
Stay away from my niece!

689
01:07:15,077 --> 01:07:17,496
Come on.
Are you all right?

690
01:08:26,565 --> 01:08:28,901
( Allison whimpering )

691
01:08:41,205 --> 01:08:43,582
Please.

692
01:08:45,125 --> 01:08:47,503
lf they have no feelings,

693
01:08:47,544 --> 01:08:49,963
they can't know fear.

694
01:08:52,007 --> 01:08:54,801
But if they can't know fear...

695
01:08:54,843 --> 01:08:57,221
( Allison panting )

696
01:08:57,221 --> 01:08:59,640
then why do they run?

697
01:09:13,737 --> 01:09:16,073
Anybody home?

698
01:09:20,994 --> 01:09:22,538
Please don't.

699
01:09:28,627 --> 01:09:30,045
Sutter!

700
01:09:31,129 --> 01:09:32,381
Uncle J!

701
01:09:33,465 --> 01:09:35,717
( whimpering )

702
01:09:51,525 --> 01:09:52,693
( knocks )

703
01:09:52,734 --> 01:09:55,237
( muffled screaming )

704
01:09:58,240 --> 01:10:00,868
Hello?

705
01:10:00,909 --> 01:10:02,619
( knocking )

706
01:10:02,661 --> 01:10:05,497
( muffled screams )

707
01:10:10,210 --> 01:10:12,629
Who's there?

708
01:10:13,630 --> 01:10:15,757
lt's Jonathan Miller.

709
01:10:15,799 --> 01:10:17,718
l'm looking for my niece.

710
01:10:17,759 --> 01:10:20,262
She didn't come home
last night.

711
01:10:20,304 --> 01:10:22,431
l've been looking
all over for her.

712
01:10:22,473 --> 01:10:24,850
l thought she might have wandered
over here. Have you seen her?

713
01:10:24,892 --> 01:10:26,643
No.

714
01:10:28,395 --> 01:10:33,317
Listen, do you have a young boy
living over here?

715
01:10:33,358 --> 01:10:36,320
She said she saw a boy
running around over here.

716
01:10:36,320 --> 01:10:38,280
Just get off my property.

717
01:10:40,324 --> 01:10:41,825
You mind if l come in
a moment?

718
01:10:41,867 --> 01:10:43,118
l'm busy.

719
01:10:43,160 --> 01:10:45,162
Just a moment.

720
01:10:46,205 --> 01:10:48,415
Just a second.

721
01:10:50,083 --> 01:10:52,085
Uncle J!

722
01:10:52,127 --> 01:10:54,171
Allison?

723
01:11:16,693 --> 01:11:19,321
Uncle J!

724
01:11:24,117 --> 01:11:26,119
What did you do?

725
01:11:26,161 --> 01:11:28,664
You girls, you--

726
01:11:28,705 --> 01:11:31,458
you never can keep
your mouths shut.

727
01:11:31,500 --> 01:11:33,752
( screaming )

728
01:11:37,214 --> 01:11:39,174
No! No!

729
01:11:39,216 --> 01:11:43,011
( continues screaming )
No. No.

730
01:11:43,053 --> 01:11:45,514
- ( grunting )
- ( screaming )

731
01:11:50,727 --> 01:11:52,521
No. No.

732
01:11:52,563 --> 01:11:55,023
( continues screaming )

733
01:12:00,863 --> 01:12:03,240
No!

734
01:12:05,409 --> 01:12:07,161
No.

735
01:12:10,080 --> 01:12:12,457
( screaming )
Leave me alone!

736
01:13:03,300 --> 01:13:05,427
( sobbing )

737
01:13:15,813 --> 01:13:17,481
( screaming )

738
01:13:30,410 --> 01:13:32,454
William: Hello?

739
01:13:34,790 --> 01:13:37,751
Allison?

740
01:13:37,793 --> 01:13:40,170
Mr. Miller?

741
01:13:45,592 --> 01:13:47,803
( chimes tinkling )

742
01:13:56,270 --> 01:13:58,313
( panting )

743
01:14:08,198 --> 01:14:10,576
Hello?

744
01:14:19,960 --> 01:14:22,004
( water dripping )

745
01:14:25,465 --> 01:14:27,176
Allison?

746
01:14:44,067 --> 01:14:45,861
( screaming )

747
01:14:56,413 --> 01:14:59,166
Oh my God. Martin!

748
01:14:59,208 --> 01:15:00,667
( silent )

749
01:15:00,709 --> 01:15:02,085
Help me!

750
01:15:03,921 --> 01:15:06,256
Open the door. Hurry.

751
01:15:09,259 --> 01:15:10,886
Come back. Help.

752
01:15:13,722 --> 01:15:17,100
Let me out, Martin.

753
01:15:17,142 --> 01:15:19,436
Allison?

754
01:15:25,567 --> 01:15:27,569
Hello.

755
01:15:49,508 --> 01:15:51,093
( knocking )
Allison.

756
01:15:52,928 --> 01:15:56,140
Can she--?
Allison.

757
01:15:56,181 --> 01:15:57,391
l can't hear you.

758
01:15:57,432 --> 01:15:59,935
William, open the door.

759
01:15:59,977 --> 01:16:02,646
- lt's locked.
- Hurry.

760
01:16:12,364 --> 01:16:13,907
William:
l think it's coming loose.

761
01:16:15,450 --> 01:16:17,536
Allison:
Turn around, please.

762
01:16:19,329 --> 01:16:21,206
Allison:
Turn around.

763
01:16:21,248 --> 01:16:24,209
l'm gonna get you out of here.
l promise. lt's okay.

764
01:16:24,251 --> 01:16:26,420
l got it.

765
01:16:26,461 --> 01:16:27,963
( Allison screams )

766
01:16:29,923 --> 01:16:31,300
( Allison screaming )

767
01:16:40,601 --> 01:16:43,353
Allison: Stop!

768
01:16:46,148 --> 01:16:48,901
( Allison screaming, crying )

769
01:17:09,087 --> 01:17:11,131
( sobbing )

770
01:17:34,571 --> 01:17:36,323
( quietly )
No.

771
01:17:38,617 --> 01:17:40,953
Forget it.

772
01:17:44,957 --> 01:17:46,708
Leave me alone.

773
01:17:59,179 --> 01:18:01,598
l don't care.

774
01:18:01,598 --> 01:18:03,934
Let them find out.

775
01:18:29,710 --> 01:18:31,962
Forget it.

776
01:18:32,004 --> 01:18:33,505
l won't do it.

777
01:18:33,547 --> 01:18:35,966
l can't.

778
01:18:40,888 --> 01:18:43,682
You leave him alone.

779
01:18:43,724 --> 01:18:46,268
He hasn't done anything.

780
01:18:47,644 --> 01:18:49,938
No. No, l need him.

781
01:18:49,980 --> 01:18:53,025
Who-- who-- who's gonna
help me clean up?

782
01:18:54,860 --> 01:18:57,154
You know l can't stand it.

783
01:18:57,196 --> 01:18:59,990
No no no
no no no no.

784
01:19:00,032 --> 01:19:03,452
Shut up. Shut up!

785
01:19:03,494 --> 01:19:05,287
God!

786
01:19:05,329 --> 01:19:07,164
You're no better than he was!

787
01:19:41,198 --> 01:19:43,826
You promised me.

788
01:19:43,867 --> 01:19:46,286
l did everything you said.

789
01:19:48,914 --> 01:19:52,209
( screams )

790
01:19:52,251 --> 01:19:54,253
( sobbing )

791
01:20:07,307 --> 01:20:09,643
You win.

792
01:20:22,239 --> 01:20:24,616
You're wrong.

793
01:20:24,658 --> 01:20:26,952
He wouldn't dare.

794
01:20:57,065 --> 01:20:59,943
Don't look at me like that.

795
01:20:59,985 --> 01:21:01,820
You don't ask why.

796
01:21:01,862 --> 01:21:04,573
You just do.

797
01:21:04,615 --> 01:21:06,909
That's just the way it is.

798
01:21:10,120 --> 01:21:13,290
You think you owe me,

799
01:21:13,332 --> 01:21:17,419
think maybe l should grow eyes
in the back of my head?

800
01:21:17,461 --> 01:21:20,088
They abandoned you.

801
01:21:22,382 --> 01:21:24,802
What would you be
without me?

802
01:21:27,596 --> 01:21:29,598
You feel guilty or something?

803
01:21:29,640 --> 01:21:33,101
Don't feel guilty.

804
01:21:33,143 --> 01:21:36,104
A child shouldn't feel guilty
about nothing.

805
01:21:45,197 --> 01:21:47,658
You--

806
01:21:47,699 --> 01:21:51,036
you don't feel anything, do you--

807
01:21:51,078 --> 01:21:53,747
guilt, pain, regret--

808
01:21:53,789 --> 01:21:57,876
nothing? Do you?

809
01:21:57,918 --> 01:22:01,171
Who are you to judge me?

810
01:22:14,852 --> 01:22:17,229
You have no soul to redeem.

811
01:22:19,398 --> 01:22:21,483
Do you?

812
01:22:30,617 --> 01:22:32,995
Don't try anything funny
while l'm gone.

813
01:22:33,036 --> 01:22:35,414
They're watching.

814
01:23:56,328 --> 01:23:58,372
( grunting )

815
01:24:17,808 --> 01:24:19,768
( panting )

816
01:24:47,671 --> 01:24:49,631
Oh my God.

817
01:24:49,673 --> 01:24:51,758
What did he do to you?

818
01:24:51,800 --> 01:24:54,470
Come on. l'm gonna get you
out of here, okay?

819
01:24:54,511 --> 01:24:55,804
l'm sorry.

820
01:25:10,027 --> 01:25:12,029
Are you okay?

821
01:25:13,405 --> 01:25:15,407
Come on.

822
01:25:17,242 --> 01:25:20,162
Come on. lt's okay.
Trust me, okay?

823
01:25:31,965 --> 01:25:35,010
Come on, l can't carry you.

824
01:25:36,595 --> 01:25:39,348
ls this what you're scared of?

825
01:25:39,389 --> 01:25:43,018
This thing?

826
01:25:44,520 --> 01:25:46,939
You see? lt's nothing.

827
01:25:59,076 --> 01:26:01,036
When are they coming home?

828
01:26:01,078 --> 01:26:02,579
Soon.

829
01:26:17,302 --> 01:26:19,471
( panting, grunting )

830
01:26:44,121 --> 01:26:46,456
( knocks on door )

831
01:26:46,498 --> 01:26:48,000
Finally.

832
01:27:01,138 --> 01:27:03,432
Yes?

833
01:27:04,433 --> 01:27:07,102
- ( screams )
- Wendy, run.

834
01:27:07,144 --> 01:27:09,938
Mommy!
( screaming )

835
01:27:12,691 --> 01:27:14,401
Mommy.

836
01:27:19,948 --> 01:27:23,035
- Mommy!
- Wendy, run.

837
01:27:23,076 --> 01:27:24,286
Run!

838
01:27:35,255 --> 01:27:36,423
No, please don't.

839
01:27:36,465 --> 01:27:38,091
l have to.

840
01:27:38,133 --> 01:27:40,135
( screaming )

841
01:27:46,892 --> 01:27:49,311
We're almost there, okay?

842
01:28:02,157 --> 01:28:04,159
( panting )

843
01:28:10,874 --> 01:28:12,876
Jonathan.

844
01:28:39,153 --> 01:28:40,654
No.

845
01:28:52,457 --> 01:28:55,502
lt's gonna be okay.

846
01:28:55,544 --> 01:28:57,129
Okay?

847
01:28:57,171 --> 01:28:59,089
l'm gonna get you home.

848
01:28:59,089 --> 01:29:01,133
( panting, whimpering )

849
01:29:01,175 --> 01:29:03,218
( scratching )

850
01:29:14,897 --> 01:29:17,107
Randy. Oh Randy.

851
01:29:18,233 --> 01:29:19,735
( screams )

852
01:29:27,117 --> 01:29:29,119
( door rattling )

853
01:29:33,373 --> 01:29:35,584
lt's gonna be okay.
lt's gonna be okay.

854
01:29:35,626 --> 01:29:37,211
( screams )

855
01:29:43,759 --> 01:29:47,429
Please don't hurt my animals.

856
01:29:53,602 --> 01:29:54,895
No.

857
01:30:10,828 --> 01:30:13,205
Ate from my hand...

858
01:30:16,416 --> 01:30:19,670
and trusted me

859
01:30:19,711 --> 01:30:22,297
even at the end.

860
01:30:24,466 --> 01:30:26,844
Unconditional.

861
01:30:26,844 --> 01:30:29,721
And he-- he made me!

862
01:30:29,763 --> 01:30:30,973
Mommy!

863
01:30:39,690 --> 01:30:41,817
l'm making things right.

864
01:30:41,859 --> 01:30:44,319
l owe them that much.

865
01:30:45,863 --> 01:30:49,616
With each one

866
01:30:49,658 --> 01:30:51,785
another sin is forgiven.

867
01:30:51,827 --> 01:30:55,330
l can't let it happen again,

868
01:30:55,372 --> 01:30:56,832
not like me.

869
01:31:03,714 --> 01:31:07,509
You understand, don't you?

870
01:31:07,551 --> 01:31:10,971
Not like that boy-- worthless.

871
01:31:12,014 --> 01:31:14,892
( screams )

872
01:31:14,892 --> 01:31:16,935
Karen!

873
01:31:20,063 --> 01:31:22,900
Karen.

874
01:31:22,941 --> 01:31:27,362
Don't let him get her.

875
01:31:32,326 --> 01:31:34,995
l can't stop now.

876
01:31:35,037 --> 01:31:37,581
There's still
so much more to do.

877
01:31:37,623 --> 01:31:39,374
You-- you come with me.

878
01:31:39,416 --> 01:31:40,959
Come with me.

879
01:31:42,544 --> 01:31:44,546
Please come with me.

880
01:31:44,588 --> 01:31:47,382
Help me.
Help me redeem myself!

881
01:31:47,424 --> 01:31:50,552
- No.
- Let her go, you son of a bitch!

882
01:31:50,594 --> 01:31:52,346
( Wendy screaming )

883
01:31:52,387 --> 01:31:54,348
( groans )

884
01:31:57,601 --> 01:31:59,937
lt does.

885
01:31:59,978 --> 01:32:02,564
l'm sorry.

886
01:32:04,066 --> 01:32:06,068
( Allison exclaims )

887
01:32:11,365 --> 01:32:13,367
lt's okay.

888
01:32:13,408 --> 01:32:16,495
lt's me.
lt's just me, okay?

889
01:32:16,537 --> 01:32:18,330
Where is Mommy?

890
01:32:18,372 --> 01:32:19,873
She's downstairs.

891
01:32:26,130 --> 01:32:28,173
l need you to stay here,
all right?

892
01:32:28,215 --> 01:32:29,383
Why?

893
01:32:29,424 --> 01:32:31,718
Just please do as l say.

894
01:32:31,760 --> 01:32:33,470
- Okay?
- Don't leave.

895
01:32:33,512 --> 01:32:36,056
l'm not leaving.
Just stay here.

896
01:32:36,098 --> 01:32:38,058
( Wendy whimpering )

897
01:32:40,936 --> 01:32:42,104
( coughing )

898
01:32:44,148 --> 01:32:46,567
( Allison screams )

899
01:32:50,654 --> 01:32:52,114
Martin!

900
01:32:58,287 --> 01:33:00,372
( sobbing )

901
01:33:06,503 --> 01:33:08,672
Martin!

902
01:33:10,466 --> 01:33:13,552
